define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_THUMBNAILPICTUREMATTES",	 '<b>Picture Color Mattes:<br><img src=icons/ThumbsMatte.gif align=left hspace=5> <p align=left>The Matte COLOR and WIDTH determines the <font color=red>colored area immediately surrounding the image.</font></p><p align=left>If you are using Picture Frame Styles (border images), this matte appears between the frame and the picture, just like a matte in real picture framing.</p>');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_COLORFONDO1",		 	'<b>Matte Color:<br><img src=icons/ThumbsMatte.gif align=left hspace=5> <p align=left>The Matte COLOR is specified as:<ul><li>A standard color number<br>(i.e. FF0080 for Hot Pink) or <li>A color name (i.e. magenta) or <li>A theme class (i.e. 1 through 6)</ul>and creates a <font color=red>colored area immediately surrounding the image</font><br>(width specified by Matte Width).</p><p align=left>If you are using Picture Frame Styles (border images), this matte appears between the frame and the picture, just like a matte in real picture framing.</p>');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_COLORFONDO2",		 	'<b>Matte Width:<br><img src=icons/ThumbsMatte.gif align=left hspace=5> <p align=left>The Matte WIDTH is specified as:<ul><li>A number of pixels (i.e. 5) </ul>and creates a <font color=red>colored area immediately surrounding the image</font> in the width specified, on each side of the image.</p><p align=left>If you are using Picture Frame Styles (border images), this matte appears between the frame and the picture, just like a matte in real picture framing.</p>');
